@node 2 "The Story So Far..."

  @{b}The Story So Far...@{ub}

  The Year is 2150. A group of astronauts blast off from Earth in the
  newest, most powerful space shuttle known to man. The shuttle can
  reach speeds of 1 Light Year per hour, which has opened many doors
  for the human race. The astronauts' mission? To find new life in
  surrounding galaxies.

  All is going well on the shuttle. The 10 man crew is adjusting to the
  way of life and lack of gravity encountered in the shuttle when
  their power supply suddenly cuts off and the shuttle is left drifting 
  towards a nearby planet. It is almost inevitable that the shuttle will
  crash on this planet.

  After impact, the 4 remaining members of the crew crawl out into the
  almost Earth-like atmosphere of this new planet. The communication
  device inside the shuttle is damaged beyond repair and it seems 
  likely that the 4 remaining crew members will stay on this planet
  until their 50 year food supply runs out.

  40 years later in the year 2190, another crew of 10 people blast off
  from earth in a shuttle almost identical to that which left Earth
  40 years ago. This time the mission is different. Earth based space
  research scientists realised that the last supplies of a very important
  metal found in space in the year 2110 were on the shuttle which
  launched in 2150. Now, the new shuttle must try to recover anything
  from the crashed ship which blast off those 40 years ago.

